# Momora Client (Expo)

## Structure

- `app/` — routes only; keep screens thin
- `src/hooks/` — data hooks (`useMemories`, `useFamilyMembers`, `useVoiceInput`)
- `src/services/` — Edge Function invocations
- `src/components/` — presentational + small composed UI

## Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Query for server state
const { data, isLoading, error } = useMemories();

// ✅ Early return for loading/error
if (isLoading) return <LoadingState />;
if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} />;

// ❌ Don't fetch in useEffect when TanStack Query fits
```

- Use `Pressable`, `expo-image`, safe area context.
- For every `TextInput`/search field in a screen, modal, bottom sheet, or drawer, add keyboard avoidance (`KeyboardAvoidingView`, keyboard-aware scroll/content insets, or the established local pattern) so focused inputs and primary actions remain visible above the keyboard on iOS and Android.
- Show illustration/portrait status: `pending | generating | ready | failed` + retry.
- Voice: tap start/stop, 2-min cap, editable transcript before save.
- Onboarding nudges **child first**; block new memory until ≥1 portrait is `ready`.
- Plain text memories only — multiline `TextInput`, no rich text.

## Lists

Virtualize timeline (`FlashList` or `FlatList`). Stable `keyExtractor`. Avoid inline objects in `renderItem`.

## Conditional render

```tsx
// ❌ Crashes if count is 0
{count && <Text>{count}</Text>}

// ✅
{count > 0 ? <Text>{count}</Text> : null}
```
